        <svcsubproc>
            <title>CHASSIS SWITCH INPUTS TO RPM'S</title>
            <para>The RPM has inputs on the module itself that can be programmed to control the outputs. The output
                channels may be controlled remotely by using a three position momentary single pole, double throw switch
                on each remote switch input. In this case, battery volts should be connected to one pole of the switch
                and ground should be connected to the other. Applying battery volts to the remote switch input shall
                turn the output channel "ON". Applying ground to the remote switch input shall turn the output channel
                off.
            </para>
